\begin_layout Standard
This document is the Requirements Analysis Specification Document (RASD)
 for Travlendar+, the system assigned to be developed on the mandatory project.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The goal of this project is to create a calendar-based application that
 benefits of this features:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Automatically computes travel time between appointments to make sure that
 the user will never be late;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Supports people providing informations about the best mobility solution;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Allow people to buy public transportation tickets or locating the nearest
 bike;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Allow people to create meetings;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Suggest travel solutions depending on the type of appointment;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Check the weather forecast in order to provide the best mobility solution;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Allow people to define various kind of preferences;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Allow people to choose whether to combine transportation means in order
 to lower carbon emissions;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Allow people to select a flexible lunch time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The scope of the project is to provide every person of a valuable tools
 that they can use in order to have a better schedule of their daily life.
 We can identify the external world as every entity, aspect or occurrence
 relevant for the case that happen unconditionally from the system and its
 utilization.
 If the occurrence could be abstracted, then it is includible in this project,
 and therefore labeled as shared phenomena.
\end_layout

